review_blob: Bottle - Deep smokey aroma off the pour; Very rich stout with a strong lingering oak flavor. Minimal tan head with no lacing. Heavy chocolate and coffee notes.

Bottle - Massive white pillow of a head. Intense carbonation in this light brown/orange pour. Aroma decent. Smooth taste with high volume of lingering esters. Drinkability not high past 12 oz. Small amount of sediment is expected. Hops masked to almost not existent for an English pale.

2009 Bottle - Great aroma off the pour. Small dark brown head, with minimal carbonation in this jet black beast. Incredible taste; Very rich, sweet stout. Great bourbon flavors cut through the chocolate and coffee, with a smooth finish.
Bottle - Dark brown pour. Great taste and initial mouthfeel. Medium tan head, with less lingering carbonation. Minimal lacing, and subtle scotch flavor. A bit too sweet. Poured aroma off-putting.
beer_name: Dragonmead Under the Kilt Wee Heavy

review_blob: First half of bottle poured clear. Great white head with no lacing. Second half was very unappealing with such heavy sediment (unfiltered).  Aroma and mouth feel true to the style. Smooth finish, good drinkablility.
